Gore (Noun) / Gory (Adjective)

Meaning- blood that has been shed, especially as a result of violence.
                - involving or showing violence and bloodshed 
Example- The movie involves gore and thus, parental discretion is advised.
                 - Mrs. Bandyopadhyay was keenly interested in the gory details. 

Pronunciation-                GORE | Pronunciation in English (cambridge.org)
                                          GORY | English meaning - Cambridge Dictionary
